  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Top, tail and chop the <strong>parsnip<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and<strong> carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>into quarters lengthways, then into batons</p><p>Peel and cut the <strong>red</strong> <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges</p><p>Strip the <strong>thyme leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634049033468-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634049033468-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634049033468-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634049033468-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634049033468-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> red onion wedges</strong>, <strong>parsnip</strong> and <strong>carrot batons </strong>and <strong>thyme leaves</strong> to a baking tray lined with <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and<strong> </strong>give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the baking tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until beginning to soften – this is your<strong> roasted veg</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634049095005-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634049095005-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634049095005-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634049095005-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634049095005-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are cooking, dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and  <strong>Henderson's Relish </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1634049106465-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1634049106465-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1634049106465-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1634049106465-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1634049106465-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) and melt a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat, then add 2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]<strong> </span>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs until a paste forms</p><p>Add the <strong>stock</strong> with half <span class=\"text-danger\">[all] </span>of the<strong> wholegrain mustard </strong>and <strong>onion marmalade</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 2? Save the remaining wholegrain mustard for another recipe!</p><p>Turn down the heat and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened – this is your<strong> onion gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1634049114253-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1634049114253-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1634049114253-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1634049114253-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1634049114253-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the tray with the roasted veg from the oven and set the veg aside</p><p>Replace the tin foil with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap the <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and cut into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> squares</p><p>Add the <strong>pastry squares</strong> to the tray and score a 1cm border around the edge of the pastry with a knife</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1634049149739-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
